This article is a press gaggle by Principal Deputy Press Secretary Josh Earnest aboard Air Force One on June 22, 2012. Earnest discusses President Obama's upcoming speech to NALEO (National Association of Latino Elected and Appointed Officials) about his efforts to help middle-class families and the economy recover from the recession. He also mentions statistics about job creation in Florida and criticizes Republicans in Congress for not acting on legislation that would put more people back to work. Earnest hints that the President will talk about immigration reform in his speech. The press also asks questions about other topics such as the Attorney General and recent books about the Obamas.